etrunk_schema.description: Enhanced Trunk (E-Trunk) is a mechanism that controls and implements link aggregation among multiple devices. E-Trunk implements device-level not board-level link reliability.

lacp-sys-id.description: Global LACP system MAC address. The default value is the mac address of the system bridge MAC address.

udp-port.description: UDP port used for global E-Trunk communication.

udp6-port.description: UDP6 port used for global E-Trunk communication.

cir.description: Specify the session CAR CIR value.

cbs.description: Specify the session CAR CBS value.

pir.description: Specify the session CAR PIR value.

pbs.description: Specify the session CAR PBS value.

cir.description: Specify the session CAR CIR value.

cbs.description: Specify the session CAR CBS value.

pir.description: Specify the session CAR PIR value.

pbs.description: Specify the session CAR PBS value.

id.description: An integer that uniquely identifies an E-Trunk link.

priority.description: The E-Trunk priority determines the master/backup status of two devices in an aggregation group.

ni-name.description: VPN instance name. If peer-addr and source-addr are set to IPv4, the IPv4 address family needs to be configured for the VPN instance. If peer-addr and source-addr are set to IPv6, the IPv6 address family needs to be configured for the VPN instance.

peer-addr.description: Configure peer IPv4/IPv6 address, peer-addr and source-addr must be of the same type, either IPv4 or IPv6.

source-addr.description: Configure source IPv4/IPv6 address, peer-addr and source-addr must be of the same type, either IPv4 or IPv6.

static-bfd.description: BFD session choice case as static BFD.

bfd-session-name.description: Bind the BFD session to an E-Trunk.

dyn-bfd.description: Dynamic BFD session binding to an E-Trunk.

min-rx-interval.description: Interval at which BFD hello packets are received.

min-tx-interval.description: Interval at which BFD hello packets are sent.

if-name.description: Tracked interface name. The interface must be a physical main interface or Eth-Trunk interface.

security-key-type.description: Configure a password type, the cipher encryption type is recommended.

security-key.description: Configure a password for encrypted packets. The password is a string ranging from 1 to 255 characters for a unencrypted password and 24 characters for an old encrypted password and 20 to 432 characters for a encrypted password.

authen-mode.description: Configure an authentication mode for an E-Trunk.

timer-hello.description: Configure the interval at which hello packets are sent.

timer-multi.description: Configure the multiplier for detecting hello packets.

description.description: Configure a description for an E-Trunk.

select-mode.description: The mode of E-Trunk that is used for calculate the active or standby status.

causation.description: The reason for local E-Trunk state change.

recv-drop-pkts.description: Statistics about dropped received packets statistics.

peer-priority.description: The E-Trunk peer priority determines the master/backup status of two devices in an aggregation group.

peer-fail-time.description: Peer timeout period. Timeout period = peer sending period x Multiplier.

interface.description:
Configure E-Trunk member.
Special explanation: Before adding an interface to an E-Trunk, you must create the interface based on localTrunkId and type.

if-name.description: Local Eth-Trunk name or Global-VE name.

causation.description: The reason for E-Trunk member state change.

lacp-priority.description: LACP system priority of the Eth-Trunk.

lacp-sysid.description: LACP system MAC of the Eth-Trunk. The default value is generated by LACP.

negotiate-delay.description: Set the value of negotiating delay time.

reason-err-pkts.description: Receive state reason error packets statistics.

peer-err-pkts.description: Receive peer IP error packets statistics.

auth-err-pkts.description: Receive authentication mode error packets statistics.

sysid-err-pkts.description: Receive system ID error packets statistics.

bfd-err-pkts.description: Receive BFD protection error packets statistics.

seq-err-pkts.description: Receive sequence check error packets statistics.
